1
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:14,366
No matter what happens,
I'll be right here by your side.

2
00:00:15,066 --> 00:00:17,090
My daughter means everything to me.

3
00:00:17,374 --> 00:00:20,900
And I can't even tell you
if I'll ever be able to accept you.

4
00:00:21,566 --> 00:00:22,751
I promise,

5
00:00:23,272 --> 00:00:25,787
that I'll protect her with my life.

6
00:00:27,666 --> 00:00:28,800
Will you marry me?

7
00:00:29,466 --> 00:00:30,266
Yes!

8
00:00:41,866 --> 00:00:43,161
Ping, sweetheart.

9
00:00:44,060 --> 00:00:46,518
I understand how happy you are

10
00:00:46,518 --> 00:00:48,810
after the proposal.

11
00:00:49,766 --> 00:00:50,597
But...

12
00:00:50,597 --> 00:00:54,522
You're trending on social media
for all the wrong reasons right now.

13
00:00:55,043 --> 00:00:58,632
The calls from the board and the shareholders

14
00:00:58,632 --> 00:01:00,565
keep my phone ringing non-stop.

15
00:01:01,038 --> 00:01:03,209
They're worried the company's image

16
00:01:03,209 --> 00:01:05,357
might take a hit, honey.

17
00:01:08,733 --> 00:01:11,100
I'm not trying to keep you two apart.

18
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:14,300
But I have to think about the company's future too.

19
00:01:14,933 --> 00:01:17,800
You're the future president of this company.

20
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:22,466
I'm afraid we'll lose the shareholders' backing.

21
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:25,400
if they still feel uncertain.

22
00:01:26,866 --> 00:01:28,333
You understand that, right?

23
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:32,200
I do, Mom.

24
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:43,600
Hello, Cher.

25
00:01:44,366 --> 00:01:46,608
Ping! I'm so happy for you!

26
00:01:46,608 --> 00:01:50,000
P'Charm's proposal was freaking romantic.

27
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,333
Thanks, Cher.

28
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:57,166
But...

29
00:01:57,666 --> 00:01:59,400
Why do you sound like that?

30
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,593
Wait—

31
00:02:00,924 --> 00:02:03,166
are those hate comments getting to you?

32
00:02:03,666 --> 00:02:05,766
I suggest you'd better tune them out.

33
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:07,766
It's not that, Cher.

34
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:10,333
It's much bigger than that.

35
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:13,558
Should we meet up tonight?

36
00:02:13,558 --> 00:02:15,000
My treat.

37
00:02:16,133 --> 00:02:17,448
Okay, Cher.

38
00:02:18,158 --> 00:02:20,666
Yeah, I have something to tell you too.

39
00:02:21,666 --> 00:02:23,933
Okay, see you then.

40
00:02:26,733 --> 00:02:27,898
Mom,

41
00:02:28,892 --> 00:02:30,445
I'll take my leave now.

42
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:31,766
Go ahead.

43
00:02:58,266 --> 00:02:59,091
Hey!

44
00:02:59,706 --> 00:03:00,536
Wait a second.

45
00:03:01,625 --> 00:03:03,234
You don't usually touch alcohol.

46
00:03:04,566 --> 00:03:06,375
I just felt like trying it.

47
00:03:07,322 --> 00:03:09,145
Maybe I'll feel better.

48
00:03:13,766 --> 00:03:14,604
So,

49
00:03:15,125 --> 00:03:17,054
what's the plan for you and P'Charm?

50
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:20,000
I don't know yet, Cher.

51
00:03:21,466 --> 00:03:23,300
If it were just the two of us,

52
00:03:23,766 --> 00:03:25,500
things wouldn't be this hard.

53
00:03:26,566 --> 00:03:28,600
But once business gets involved,

54
00:03:29,933 --> 00:03:33,133
everything just gets so complicated.

55
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:37,966
True, and you're an only child.

56
00:03:42,266 --> 00:03:43,383
But...

57
00:03:43,667 --> 00:03:46,484
considering everything
you and P'Charm have been through,

58
00:03:48,966 --> 00:03:51,900
you've survived a lot.

59
00:03:55,766 --> 00:03:57,266
You'll definitely get through this.

60
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:58,933
Trust me.

61
00:04:13,829 --> 00:04:14,971
Look, you're making a mess.

62
00:04:15,539 --> 00:04:16,545
Are you okay?

63
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:35,117
Hello, P'Charm.

64
00:04:35,543 --> 00:04:36,759
It's Cher.

65
00:04:37,066 --> 00:04:40,133
Oh, Cher. Where's Ping?

66
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:42,778
P'Charm, could you come pick her up?

67
00:04:42,778 --> 00:04:44,200
She's wasted.

68
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:45,933
She's actually drunk?

69
00:04:47,066 --> 00:04:47,668
Yeah.

70
00:04:48,662 --> 00:04:50,454
She's a bit stressed out.

71
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:51,637
But...

72
00:04:51,637 --> 00:04:53,637
I'll let her tell you herself.

73
00:04:55,152 --> 00:04:57,463
Just come get her, okay?

74
00:04:58,268 --> 00:04:59,780
I'll send you the location.

75
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,333
Got it. Thanks, Khun Cher.

76
00:05:03,133 --> 00:05:03,933
No problem.

77
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,900
Oh, Ping... honestly.

78
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:18,133
That's enough.

79
00:05:28,066 --> 00:05:28,866
Easy now.

80
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:53,180
What were you thinking,

81
00:05:54,127 --> 00:05:55,808
getting this drunk?

82
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,200
P'Charm...

83
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:06,966
what should we do?

84
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:11,100
So I can marry you

85
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:15,600
without all this drama.

86
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,713
It's okay.

87
00:06:26,039 --> 00:06:29,345
Drink some water, honey.

88
00:07:06,966 --> 00:07:09,100
P'Charm, do you love me?

89
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:13,333
Of course I do.

90
00:07:18,366 --> 00:07:20,333
Feeling better now, babe?

91
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:24,000
P'Charm...

92
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:29,333
Mom called me in for a talk.

93
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:33,766
She said if we get married,

94
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:38,400
it could hurt the company's credibility.

95
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,166
What are we going to do?

96
00:07:54,366 --> 00:07:55,700
Don't worry, Ping.

97
00:07:57,966 --> 00:07:58,997
As for this,

98
00:08:00,748 --> 00:08:02,492
I'll handle it.

99
00:08:18,766 --> 00:08:20,269
P'Charm...

100
00:08:21,169 --> 00:08:23,600
Can I have a kiss?

101
00:08:33,166 --> 00:08:33,966
Not like that.

102
00:08:34,966 --> 00:08:37,200
That's just a little kid's kiss.

103
00:08:38,166 --> 00:08:40,000
I want a grown-up one.

104
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:51,300
More...

105
00:08:54,166 --> 00:08:54,966
Again...

106
00:09:07,866 --> 00:09:10,133
Don't go.

107
00:09:12,866 --> 00:09:14,200
Kiss me again.

108
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,400
One more kiss.

109
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,400
Phew...

110
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:45,533
Oh, Charm.

111
00:10:46,266 --> 00:10:47,066
Drinking again?

112
00:10:47,466 --> 00:10:48,900
I thought you were slowing down.

113
00:10:49,666 --> 00:10:50,666
How can someone so gorgeous

114
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:52,066
be such a total mess?

115
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:56,666
I'm just so stressed.

116
00:10:59,066 --> 00:11:00,666
Why is marrying the one you love

117
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:03,733
so damn hard?

118
00:11:04,366 --> 00:11:07,000
It's not like I'm broke or anything.

119
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:09,066
How much do I need

120
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,733
to be good enough for her?

121
00:11:17,466 --> 00:11:18,252
Maybe...

122
00:11:19,719 --> 00:11:20,944
Should we just elope?

123
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:30,099
Hey.

124
00:11:30,099 --> 00:11:33,729
Have you even asked
if she’d actually go with you?

125
00:11:35,717 --> 00:11:38,038
And stop reading those social media posts.

126
00:11:38,369 --> 00:11:40,277
You've been in this industry for years.

127
00:11:40,703 --> 00:11:42,948
You should know how it works by now.

128
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,447
So...

129
00:11:49,577 --> 00:11:51,190
what am I supposed to do?

130
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,194
Charm.

131
00:11:56,431 --> 00:11:57,605
I'm serious.

132
00:11:57,936 --> 00:11:59,842
You seriously don't know what to do?

133
00:12:00,931 --> 00:12:02,514
You've got a major trump card.

134
00:12:03,035 --> 00:12:04,625
I think it's time you used it.

135
00:12:05,700 --> 00:12:06,666
What trump card?

136
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:14,000
Did you forget who your stepfather, Steve, is?

137
00:12:15,866 --> 00:12:19,400
Since the issue is their lack of faith in your status,

138
00:12:20,866 --> 00:12:21,666
I'd say

139
00:12:22,733 --> 00:12:26,133
it's time to reveal who you truly are.

140
00:12:28,166 --> 00:12:31,533
This is getting exciting. It's like a soap opera!

141
00:12:35,666 --> 00:12:37,366
Wouldn't that hurt my pride?

142
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,666
Every time I see him,

143
00:12:40,066 --> 00:12:41,900
I just give him the cold shoulder.

144
00:12:43,066 --> 00:12:44,700
And now I have to ask for his help?

145
00:12:48,933 --> 00:12:52,776
Then just cuddle your ego instead of your wife.

146
00:12:53,297 --> 00:12:54,000
Happy now?

147
00:12:54,426 --> 00:12:55,448
Cuddle your ego instead.

148
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,481
For her.

149
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:04,900
For love.

150
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:10,400
Steve.

151
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:12,100
Steve!

152
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:42,133
Mom!

153
00:13:45,666 --> 00:13:48,533
I'm so sorry I couldn't pick you up.

154
00:13:48,933 --> 00:13:51,000
Oh, don't worry about it. It's fine.

155
00:13:51,666 --> 00:13:52,933
I missed you so much, Mom.

156
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:54,966
I missed you too, dear.

157
00:14:02,566 --> 00:14:03,366
Come on, Mom.

158
00:14:03,733 --> 00:14:04,267
Have a seat.

159
00:14:04,267 --> 00:14:04,900
Alright.

160
00:14:08,133 --> 00:14:08,933
Thank you.

161
00:14:16,733 --> 00:14:17,652
Mom...

162
00:14:19,025 --> 00:14:20,174
Well...

163
00:14:23,771 --> 00:14:25,026
I...

164
00:14:26,162 --> 00:14:27,965
please thank Steve for me.

165
00:14:31,183 --> 00:14:32,947
For helping me out with all this.

166
00:14:39,666 --> 00:14:41,294
It's no trouble at all.

167
00:14:41,957 --> 00:14:45,417
Steve and I would do anything for you.

168
00:14:47,133 --> 00:14:48,955
And I'm so glad

169
00:14:49,712 --> 00:14:51,102
that my Charm

170
00:14:51,765 --> 00:14:53,334
is finally opening up.

171
00:14:53,855 --> 00:14:55,836
Thank you so much, honey.

172
00:15:01,566 --> 00:15:02,465
Mom,

173
00:15:04,879 --> 00:15:05,790
I think

174
00:15:06,689 --> 00:15:08,437
I only truly understood it today.

175
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,908
That family...

176
00:15:12,618 --> 00:15:14,013
doesn't necessarily mean

177
00:15:14,865 --> 00:15:16,968
sharing the same blood.

178
00:15:19,166 --> 00:15:20,109
It's just about

179
00:15:21,055 --> 00:15:23,249
someone who never lets go,

180
00:15:24,527 --> 00:15:25,965
and always looks out for you,

181
00:15:27,574 --> 00:15:29,549
no matter what happens.

182
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,564
Are you hungry yet, Mom?

183
00:15:36,564 --> 00:15:38,616
I've ordered some food.

184
00:15:38,616 --> 00:15:39,666
It should be here soon.

185
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,160
Then,

186
00:15:42,491 --> 00:15:45,333
I'll go get the plates ready.

187
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:46,700
Okay.

188
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:02,966
Hello, Khun Pornpima.

189
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:05,366
I'm Steve Brandon.

190
00:16:12,166 --> 00:16:15,800
Are you really the Chairman
of Brandon Department Store?

191
00:16:16,933 --> 00:16:17,733
Yes, I am.

192
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:38,266
Congratulations, truly.

193
00:16:38,533 --> 00:16:41,666
This news won't affect the company's image at all.

194
00:16:42,133 --> 00:16:44,362
In fact, it will even boost confidence

195
00:16:44,362 --> 00:16:45,466
even more.

196
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:47,866
As for the wedding,

197
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:51,733
we are ready to give our full support.

198
00:17:08,966 --> 00:17:09,900
P'Charm!

199
00:17:13,266 --> 00:17:14,913
When I was trying on the dress,

200
00:17:15,244 --> 00:17:16,431
how did I look?

201
00:17:17,333 --> 00:17:18,075
You looked stunning.

202
00:17:18,596 --> 00:17:19,723
So beautiful that...

203
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:22,366
I want to marry you right this second.

204
00:17:24,666 --> 00:17:26,566
You should go change too, P'Charm.

205
00:17:26,866 --> 00:17:28,466
I'm dying to see you in it.

206
00:17:30,001 --> 00:17:30,968
Coming.

207
00:18:27,566 --> 00:18:29,945
I might not be perfect,

208
00:18:31,791 --> 00:18:33,703
but having you

209
00:18:34,460 --> 00:18:35,863
right by my side...

210
00:18:37,425 --> 00:18:38,544
I feel like

211
00:18:39,254 --> 00:18:41,587
I'm the luckiest person in the world.

212
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:45,841
Thank you

213
00:18:46,267 --> 00:18:47,691
for forgiving me.

214
00:18:49,395 --> 00:18:51,054
Thank you for coming back.

215
00:18:53,766 --> 00:18:54,869
Thank you

216
00:18:55,627 --> 00:18:57,587
for choosing me again.

217
00:18:59,575 --> 00:19:00,906
I promise,

218
00:19:02,941 --> 00:19:03,948
I will love

219
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:06,637
and take care of you

220
00:19:08,483 --> 00:19:10,282
with my life.

221
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,805
P'Charm...

222
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:04,370
do you know?

223
00:20:05,979 --> 00:20:08,014
Through everything we've been through,

224
00:20:09,245 --> 00:20:10,900
no matter how hard it got...

225
00:20:13,533 --> 00:20:15,536
I always felt that

226
00:20:16,625 --> 00:20:18,093
in my heart,

227
00:20:19,418 --> 00:20:22,003
no one could ever replace you.

228
00:20:25,666 --> 00:20:26,928
Thank you

229
00:20:28,726 --> 00:20:30,693
for never letting me go.

230
00:20:32,681 --> 00:20:33,949
Thank you

231
00:20:34,990 --> 00:20:37,339
for standing up for our love.

232
00:20:42,966 --> 00:20:44,866
I love you the most, P'Charm.

233
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:50,333
And I'll love you for the rest of my life.

234
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:30,800
Are you blushing?

235
00:22:32,733 --> 00:22:34,066
Why start blushing now?

236
00:22:51,733 --> 00:22:53,859
Tonight, I'm going to show you

237
00:22:55,184 --> 00:22:57,594
just how much I love you.

238
00:23:11,248 --> 00:23:12,267
You naughty girl.

239
00:23:13,734 --> 00:23:14,920
Well, now it's my turn.

240
00:23:15,630 --> 00:23:17,639
Time for some payback.

241
00:23:18,112 --> 00:23:19,207
Tonight,

242
00:23:20,366 --> 00:23:21,166
you won't be getting any sleep.

243
00:23:23,966 --> 00:23:24,766
Let's go.

244
00:23:24,900 --> 00:23:25,400
Hmm?

245
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:26,133
Let's go.

246
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,300
Morning, babe.

247
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:26,624
How can anyone

248
00:24:27,334 --> 00:24:29,561
be this cute right when they wake up?

249
00:24:31,100 --> 00:24:32,164
P'Charm...

250
00:24:33,300 --> 00:24:35,643
teasing me so early.

251
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:39,394
I'm just so happy

252
00:24:39,394 --> 00:24:40,954
that from now on,

253
00:24:42,279 --> 00:24:44,490
we get to wake up to each other's faces

254
00:24:45,295 --> 00:24:45,990
every single morning.

255
00:24:49,398 --> 00:24:50,585
And also...

256
00:24:52,525 --> 00:24:53,626
I get to

257
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:57,333
nibble on you too.

258
00:24:57,933 --> 00:24:58,733
P'Charm!

259
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:01,700
Like this...

260
00:25:02,766 --> 00:25:05,100
I'll be covered in bruises!

261
00:25:05,966 --> 00:25:06,766
What?

262
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:08,966
I can tell you like it.

263
00:25:09,866 --> 00:25:10,600
P'Charm!

264
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:11,400
Am I wrong?

265
00:25:11,866 --> 00:25:12,666
Who said that?

266
00:25:13,366 --> 00:25:14,266
And who was the one saying,

267
00:25:15,266 --> 00:25:18,466
Don't stop, P'Charm... please, don't stop.

268
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:19,400
P'Charm!

269
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:22,766
That's enough,
I don't want to talk about this anymore.

270
00:25:24,533 --> 00:25:26,980
Let's hurry up and shower,

271
00:25:26,980 --> 00:25:29,586
then go buy some things for the house.

272
00:25:30,249 --> 00:25:32,330
And let's go pick up Charmie too.

273
00:25:32,330 --> 00:25:35,314
I'm dying to see Charmie.

274
00:25:37,349 --> 00:25:38,225
Alright.

275
00:25:38,982 --> 00:25:42,159
So, after we're done shopping

276
00:25:43,066 --> 00:25:44,333
and picking up Charmie,

277
00:25:45,866 --> 00:25:46,798
then...

278
00:25:48,076 --> 00:25:49,053
let's hurry back home.

279
00:25:50,966 --> 00:25:52,700
There's something I want to do at home.

280
00:25:53,800 --> 00:25:54,600
What is it?

281
00:25:55,366 --> 00:25:56,166
Well...

282
00:25:59,766 --> 00:26:00,687
Let's see...

283
00:26:02,770 --> 00:26:03,893
P'Charm!

284
00:26:28,700 --> 00:26:30,200
Are you done showering?

285
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:32,900
I thought I'd join you.

286
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:35,000
No way.

287
00:26:36,566 --> 00:26:38,700
Every time I shower with you...

288
00:26:40,533 --> 00:26:41,333
Why?

289
00:27:08,333 --> 00:27:09,600
I wonder why.

290
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,701
Even though we're married,

291
00:27:12,269 --> 00:27:16,768
our hearts still race like we keep falling in love.

292
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:26,000
Okay, I'll stop teasing you.

293
00:27:29,966 --> 00:27:31,400
Your skin is already perfect.

294
00:27:32,366 --> 00:27:33,933
No need for foundation today.

295
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:35,900
Looking natural like this...

296
00:27:37,300 --> 00:27:38,100
you're already beautiful.

297
00:27:40,266 --> 00:27:41,766
Thank you, P'Charm.

298
00:27:57,466 --> 00:27:58,300
P'Charm...

299
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:02,166
shouldn't you button up a bit?

300
00:28:08,133 --> 00:28:08,933
Why?

301
00:28:11,300 --> 00:28:12,133
Feeling possessive?

302
00:28:13,566 --> 00:28:14,533
Mhmm.

303
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:17,700
Up to you.

304
00:28:18,333 --> 00:28:19,500
Don't button it, then.

305
00:28:26,100 --> 00:28:26,966
You're the absolute cutest.

306
00:28:36,066 --> 00:28:36,866
Let's go.

307
00:28:48,733 --> 00:28:49,766
I never thought

308
00:28:51,100 --> 00:28:52,900
that going shopping with you

309
00:28:53,766 --> 00:28:55,733
would make me this happy.

310
00:28:57,366 --> 00:28:58,500
Me too.

311
00:28:59,566 --> 00:29:00,700
I'm so happy.

312
00:29:02,666 --> 00:29:04,100
I want to go home now.

313
00:29:05,266 --> 00:29:06,866
What did you say, P'Charm?

314
00:29:09,900 --> 00:29:10,700
Uh,

315
00:29:11,366 --> 00:29:12,300
nothing.

316
00:29:20,866 --> 00:29:23,600
Excuse me, P'Charm, P'Ping,
can we take a picture with you?

317
00:29:24,366 --> 00:29:26,800
Sure, come take a picture.

318
00:29:36,300 --> 00:29:38,166
Thank you for remembering us.

319
00:29:39,266 --> 00:29:40,066
Thank you.

320
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:50,944
Who would've thought

321
00:29:50,944 --> 00:29:53,939
that true happiness could be this simple?

322
00:29:54,318 --> 00:29:56,199
Just holding your hand, P'Charm,

323
00:29:56,672 --> 00:29:58,705
living a normal life together...

324
00:29:58,942 --> 00:30:00,974
this world is already beautiful enough.

325
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:10,066
Hello, Mom and Dad.

326
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:10,937
Hello.

327
00:30:10,937 --> 00:30:11,437
Hello.

328
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:12,400
Hello.

329
00:30:13,100 --> 00:30:15,179
Charmie!

330
00:30:16,366 --> 00:30:18,333
Greeting the cat before your own mother?

331
00:30:18,666 --> 00:30:19,500
Greet me too.

332
00:30:20,300 --> 00:30:21,366
I missed you the most.

333
00:30:22,300 --> 00:30:23,566
I missed you too, sweetie.

334
00:30:24,333 --> 00:30:25,818
Mom,

335
00:30:25,818 --> 00:30:28,119
I was only gone for a week.

336
00:30:28,119 --> 00:30:31,333
I'll see you every day once I go back to work.

337
00:30:31,866 --> 00:30:33,382
Of course I missed you.

338
00:30:33,382 --> 00:30:34,166
I missed you too.

339
00:30:37,500 --> 00:30:38,420
By the way,

340
00:30:38,420 --> 00:30:41,789
you said Charmie looks like me.

341
00:30:42,404 --> 00:30:44,148
How so?

342
00:30:49,733 --> 00:30:52,333
Literally everywhere.

343
00:30:54,533 --> 00:30:55,333
What?

344
00:30:56,500 --> 00:30:58,133
I think I'm much cuter.

345
00:30:59,466 --> 00:31:01,800
And I don't have a chubby belly like this.

346
00:31:02,566 --> 00:31:04,166
Charmie doesn't have a chubby belly.

347
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,232
Yes, he does.

348
00:31:08,752 --> 00:31:09,860
Mom, Dad...

349
00:31:10,191 --> 00:31:12,864
we should get going now.

350
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:13,541
Oh?

351
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:17,579
Aren't you staying for dinner, Ping, Charm?

352
00:31:18,300 --> 00:31:21,666
We're going to cook dinner tonight.

353
00:31:22,066 --> 00:31:22,866
Huh?

354
00:31:23,700 --> 00:31:25,333
Am I hearing things?

355
00:31:25,566 --> 00:31:27,333
You're cooking?

356
00:31:27,700 --> 00:31:28,500
Oh, Mom...

357
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:29,800
Huh.

358
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:31,866
Why, Mom?

359
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:34,366
She told me she's going to cook for me.

360
00:31:34,966 --> 00:31:37,300
I thought she cooks all the time.

361
00:31:38,700 --> 00:31:42,212
Well, once you taste her cooking,

362
00:31:42,212 --> 00:31:44,500
let me know how it goes.

363
00:31:45,333 --> 00:31:46,133
Mom!

364
00:31:47,500 --> 00:31:48,733
See you later, kids.

365
00:31:49,066 --> 00:31:49,866
Okay.

366
00:31:50,466 --> 00:31:51,366
Love you, Mom and Dad.

367
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:52,700
Love you too, dear.

368
00:31:53,066 --> 00:31:55,533
Come here, Charmie. I missed you so much.

369
00:31:56,500 --> 00:31:57,733
Charmie, don't be stubborn.

370
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:58,785
Let's see...

371
00:31:58,785 --> 00:31:59,285
Here.

372
00:32:00,166 --> 00:32:01,266
Let Mommy take a picture of you.

373
00:32:06,519 --> 00:32:07,682
Charmie,

374
00:32:07,682 --> 00:32:08,476
look here, baby.

375
00:32:08,476 --> 00:32:09,213
Charm, look here.

376
00:32:09,213 --> 00:32:10,503
One, two...

377
00:32:10,503 --> 00:32:11,746
Hold the pose for Mommy.

378
00:32:11,983 --> 00:32:13,098
Okay, one...

379
00:32:13,382 --> 00:32:14,222
two...

380
00:32:50,600 --> 00:32:52,126
P'Charm...

381
00:32:52,457 --> 00:32:55,097
I'm trying my best here.

382
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:56,713
Why is it taking so long?

383
00:32:57,376 --> 00:32:59,329
I'm waiting to eat.

384
00:32:59,966 --> 00:33:02,666
P'Charm, go sit and wait properly.

385
00:33:05,766 --> 00:33:06,800
Hurry up, behave.

386
00:33:07,366 --> 00:33:08,166
Mhmm.

387
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:10,466
Hmm, stubborn?

388
00:33:11,333 --> 00:33:12,066
Take this!

389
00:33:12,066 --> 00:33:12,866
Come here!

390
00:33:13,266 --> 00:33:14,066
Spin.

391
00:33:14,500 --> 00:33:15,299
Go on.

392
00:33:15,299 --> 00:33:15,799
Mhmm.

393
00:33:15,866 --> 00:33:16,542
Spin.

394
00:33:16,542 --> 00:33:17,042
Mhmm.

395
00:33:17,042 --> 00:33:17,542
Walk.

396
00:33:20,266 --> 00:33:21,200
Sit nicely.

397
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:23,700
Hup!

398
00:33:29,900 --> 00:33:31,081
P'Charm...

399
00:33:31,081 --> 00:33:32,066
I'm sorry.

400
00:33:33,133 --> 00:33:35,333
I didn't think it'd be this hard.

401
00:33:36,700 --> 00:33:39,066
You'll just have to eat an omelet today.

402
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,869
Your omelet

403
00:33:43,579 --> 00:33:45,776
looks like the most delicious thing in the world.

404
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:50,925
It's okay.

405
00:33:51,304 --> 00:33:53,979
I ordered some more food too.

406
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:59,266
They're all your favorites.

407
00:34:03,100 --> 00:34:03,900
This too.

408
00:34:04,566 --> 00:34:05,366
Here.

409
00:34:09,300 --> 00:34:10,100
Thank you.

410
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:14,800
Let me taste it.

411
00:34:21,866 --> 00:34:22,666
Mmm.

412
00:34:23,733 --> 00:34:24,533
It's so delicious.

413
00:34:26,533 --> 00:34:27,366
P'Charm...

414
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:29,304
Heh.

415
00:34:29,304 --> 00:34:31,166
You don't have to lie to please me.

416
00:34:33,300 --> 00:34:34,666
I'm not lying.

417
00:34:35,500 --> 00:34:36,866
I really mean it.

418
00:34:38,300 --> 00:34:41,400
This omelet, you made with heart just for me.

419
00:34:45,733 --> 00:34:46,652
And...

420
00:34:47,646 --> 00:34:49,350
the chef is delicious too.

421
00:34:50,966 --> 00:34:51,776
P'Charm!

422
00:34:53,533 --> 00:34:54,333
Talking like that...

423
00:34:55,700 --> 00:34:57,900
should I make it for you every day?

424
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:00,835
Uh...

425
00:35:01,166 --> 00:35:02,206
I think...

426
00:35:02,632 --> 00:35:03,993
maybe not.

427
00:35:03,993 --> 00:35:06,033
If you cook for me every day,

428
00:35:06,270 --> 00:35:08,879
I think I'll get fat.

429
00:35:11,766 --> 00:35:14,366
Are you tired?

430
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:16,800
No, just a little bit.

431
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:24,014
I'm so glad

432
00:35:24,392 --> 00:35:25,911
to have you here.

433
00:35:27,100 --> 00:35:29,133
Honestly, you don't have to do anything.

434
00:35:29,666 --> 00:35:31,400
Just having you by my side like this,

435
00:35:32,266 --> 00:35:34,466
I'm already the happiest person in the world.

436
00:35:36,123 --> 00:35:37,205
Then...

437
00:35:39,966 --> 00:35:41,566
should we go take a shower?

438
00:36:09,366 --> 00:36:10,700
Just relax.

439
00:36:12,300 --> 00:36:13,280
Tonight,

440
00:36:14,037 --> 00:36:16,690
I'll help you unwind.

441
00:36:23,466 --> 00:36:24,533
Do you know?

442
00:36:25,266 --> 00:36:26,066
You're beautiful,

443
00:36:27,500 --> 00:36:28,485
and...

444
00:36:29,195 --> 00:36:30,821
incredibly sexy too.

445
00:36:32,133 --> 00:36:33,933
I won't allow anyone else to see you like this.

446
00:36:34,700 --> 00:36:35,500
Only I get to see,

447
00:36:36,866 --> 00:36:38,766
only I get to do this to you.

448
00:36:40,733 --> 00:36:42,479
Who was it that said

449
00:36:43,378 --> 00:36:45,353
they didn't like showering with me?

450
00:36:46,016 --> 00:36:47,358
Then...

451
00:36:47,973 --> 00:36:49,678
maybe I should stop?

452
00:36:50,333 --> 00:36:51,516
No, don't stop.

453
00:36:51,942 --> 00:36:53,937
Let's keep showering.

454
00:37:03,166 --> 00:37:04,400
I love you.

455
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:08,166
I love bathing you the most.

456
00:37:09,300 --> 00:37:10,600
Let's shower like this every day.

457
00:38:08,733 --> 00:38:09,934
P'Charm...

458
00:38:11,590 --> 00:38:13,292
Do you think...

459
00:38:14,617 --> 00:38:16,907
we'll love each other like this forever?

460
00:38:19,966 --> 00:38:21,200
I'm so scared.

461
00:38:25,933 --> 00:38:27,333
I don't know either.

462
00:38:28,966 --> 00:38:30,366
What the future holds.

463
00:38:33,300 --> 00:38:35,269
But I will make every day

464
00:38:36,074 --> 00:38:37,938
the best it can be.

465
00:38:38,900 --> 00:38:40,200
You don't have to be scared.

466
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:44,066
No matter how many Valentines,

467
00:38:45,500 --> 00:38:46,300
how many months,

468
00:38:47,366 --> 00:38:48,166
how many years,

469
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:51,566
I will always love you,

470
00:38:52,300 --> 00:38:53,566
love only you.

471
00:39:10,500 --> 00:39:11,454
Let me

472
00:39:13,300 --> 00:39:15,358
make you happy for a change, P'Charm?

473
00:40:56,733 --> 00:40:57,993
I never thought

474
00:40:59,366 --> 00:41:02,233
we'd be walking here together again

475
00:41:02,990 --> 00:41:04,032
like this.

476
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:08,400
True.

477
00:41:11,533 --> 00:41:13,366
But looking back,

478
00:41:15,366 --> 00:41:17,500
I still feel guilty towards you.

479
00:41:18,933 --> 00:41:19,733
P'Charm.

480
00:41:20,566 --> 00:41:21,466
I'm sorry.

481
00:41:23,166 --> 00:41:25,866
How many times have you apologized?

482
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:30,664
It's really okay.

483
00:41:31,753 --> 00:41:33,060
Honestly,

484
00:41:34,433 --> 00:41:35,989
if that hadn't happened that day,

485
00:41:37,503 --> 00:41:39,817
we probably wouldn't
be loving each other like this.

486
00:41:41,533 --> 00:41:42,333
Right?

487
00:41:42,966 --> 00:41:43,766
Yeah.

488
00:41:47,133 --> 00:41:48,000
P'Charm...

489
00:41:48,600 --> 00:41:49,100
Yes?

490
00:41:49,100 --> 00:41:50,266
Look at that girl.

491
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:57,933
What do you think she's feeling right now?

492
00:42:04,700 --> 00:42:05,925
I think

493
00:42:06,162 --> 00:42:09,903
she's gathering all her courage.

494
00:42:18,800 --> 00:42:19,853
Excuse me.

495
00:42:21,935 --> 00:42:23,173
You...

496
00:42:23,694 --> 00:42:24,937
What's your name?

497
00:42:25,666 --> 00:42:27,634
Uh, I'm...

498
00:42:27,634 --> 00:42:29,000
My name is Prim.

499
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:31,200
You...

500
00:42:34,366 --> 00:42:36,266
you want to give him something, right?

501
00:42:37,666 --> 00:42:41,328
Uh, well...

502
00:42:42,464 --> 00:42:43,560
Yes.

503
00:42:43,891 --> 00:42:47,192
But I'm afraid he won't want it.

504
00:42:50,100 --> 00:42:51,277
Be brave.

505
00:42:52,224 --> 00:42:53,479
Even if he doesn't accept it,

506
00:42:53,810 --> 00:42:54,929
it's okay.

507
00:42:55,260 --> 00:42:56,930
At least

508
00:42:57,545 --> 00:43:00,000
you got to do what your heart wanted.

509
00:43:04,933 --> 00:43:06,266
Thank you, Auntie.

510
00:43:14,100 --> 00:43:14,900
Auntie?

511
00:43:35,333 --> 00:43:36,133
That was so sweet.

512
00:43:58,966 --> 00:43:59,766
P'Charm...

513
00:44:08,566 --> 00:44:09,933
Happy Valentine's Day.

514
00:44:20,766 --> 00:44:21,566
So cute.

515
00:44:22,400 --> 00:44:23,800
Thank you, Auntie.

516
00:45:15,133 --> 00:45:16,533
Today feels like a dream.

517
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:20,000
I never thought I'd see you again, P'Charm.

518
00:45:22,333 --> 00:45:23,133
For me,

519
00:45:25,166 --> 00:45:28,466
it's felt like a dream since the moment
you walked through that door.

520
00:45:32,666 --> 00:45:34,382
I never thought

521
00:45:34,903 --> 00:45:36,491
that my crush

522
00:45:38,006 --> 00:45:39,796
would be standing right in front of me.

523
00:45:40,166 --> 00:45:41,966
You still remember, P'Charm?

524
00:45:42,766 --> 00:45:43,766
I've never forgotten.

525
00:45:45,100 --> 00:45:46,097
Do you know?

526
00:45:46,571 --> 00:45:48,497
Throughout all these years,

527
00:45:50,379 --> 00:45:52,104
I kept asking myself

528
00:45:53,571 --> 00:45:55,021
how I

529
00:45:56,333 --> 00:45:58,100
would confess my feelings to you.

530
00:45:59,866 --> 00:46:00,966
And now?

531
00:46:02,333 --> 00:46:03,566
I miss everything about it.

532
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:23,000
P'Charm...

533
00:46:27,133 --> 00:46:28,766
how much do you miss me?

534
00:46:31,933 --> 00:46:32,733
I...

535
00:46:35,900 --> 00:46:37,766
miss every inch of your body.

536
00:46:40,700 --> 00:46:41,766
Which part?

537
00:46:43,900 --> 00:46:46,133
This part?

538
00:46:49,100 --> 00:46:49,900
This part?

539
00:46:52,600 --> 00:46:53,700
Or maybe...

540
00:46:56,700 --> 00:46:57,500
this part?

541
00:47:03,666 --> 00:47:04,600
P'Charm...

542
00:47:07,466 --> 00:47:08,266
what are you doing?

543
00:47:11,600 --> 00:47:13,366
Let me be the one to start.

544
00:49:12,486 --> 00:49:13,608
Back then, as a shy nerd,
I stood with a Valentine's gift,

545
00:49:13,608 --> 00:49:14,778
too scared to say a word to P’Charm.

546
00:49:14,778 --> 00:49:16,209
Unbelievably, that was the start
of our entire journey.

547
00:49:16,209 --> 00:49:17,972
Through fear and pressure,
we were once driven apart.

548
00:49:18,020 --> 00:49:19,041
Yet in the end,
we still chose one another.

549
00:49:19,041 --> 00:49:19,999
I’ve learned that true love means never letting go,

550
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:20,994
no matter the obstacles.

551
00:49:20,994 --> 00:49:21,897
I’m not that girl anymore,

552
00:49:21,897 --> 00:49:22,959
but no matter how many Valentines pass,
my heart still races.

553
00:49:22,959 --> 00:49:23,894
I love P’Charm as much as ever,
and more with each passing day.

